 colum to get (3,3,-1).
 So (2,1,0,1) is a particular solution.
 (We could also use backsubstitution on the pivot columns.) So the complete
 solution is: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\boxed{\left\{ \begin{pmatrix}2\\
1\\
0\\
1
\end{pmatrix}+t\begin{pmatrix}1\\
1\\
1\\
0
\end{pmatrix}:t\in\mathbb{R}\right\} }
\]

\end_inset

